HT|e|CS|5|AT|^-
{          Movie Maker's Prerogative          }
^-|
HT|f|cp||AT|
^B@2^Y@3I loved the first seven chapters ^*Ifrom Slam bidding Made Easier^*N by Marty Bergen. The entire book great but for now what I need is a reasonably easy but accurate hand evaluation method. Bergen's method is easy to understand but difficult to remember its five components. I had to find some way to overcome my senior momentosis and remember them. Half way through the first 7 chapters I came with a "FORMULA" which could help me remember them all. I sent my formula to Howard for review and second opinion. He modified it and my final formula became:|CP|5|AT|
^-
(A + L + Q) - D = SP
^-|CP||AT|
Howard liked the idea and I started preparing a movie on it for its release after his lessons. However, the "Adjust-3" became hard to deal with. As you notice, Howard, in his lesson, placed Adjust-3 last in the list. He in fact suggested that for early on not to worry about it because it is hard to deal with and hands needing Adjust-3 appears infrequently. I agree with the last two premises but.

But, I feel different on how to deal with Adjust-3.  Early and quickly, I like to deal with it if there is a problem or a difficulty. Just as in bridge I like to lose the tricks I must early rather than late. Therefore. I combined the first two of his components (Raw HCP and Adjust-3) in one and called it "adjusted HCP count" or "|cp|5|at|A|cp||at|" which is the Raw HCP after gone through the process of Adjust-3. You can call it "laundered HCP" if you will. The rest are easy. I have to remember that "|cp|5|at|L|cp||at|" stands for (|cp|5|at|L|cp||at|)ength point, "|cp|5|at|Q|cp||at|" stands for (|cp|5|at|Q|cp||at|)uality suit point and finally "|cp|5|at|D|cp||at|" stands for (|cp|5|at|D|cp||at|)ubious honors -Dubious Doubletons/Singletons. 

I am sure Howard would allow a report from the minority (real minority) bench and as I have spent a lot of time preparing the movie on my formula and as long as I have a captive audience I would like to share it with you. |
